This anvil appears to be specifically designed to alter certain helms.
Forged by the followers of Selena, this armor provides magical protection and the glowing Light of Truth for all who wear it.
The magical chains forged from the Black Hills are capable of calling forth the very rock of their birth to protect the wearer.
While adding to a skilled bard's performance ability, this garb has enthralling magic of it's own to offer.
The magics of this garb both protect the monk from damage and allow him to hit harder and faster.
This belt offer's the Goddess's wisdom, power and protection. Only those in tune with nature may use it.

Imbued with elven magics, the wearer of this armor can move more freely than if he were clad in nothing at all.

Forged from Black Hills metals in a secret combination, this axe hungers for the blood of the enemies of the Khazad.
Crafted by the master Montoya in the mysterious far-off land known only as "Spain", this blade was built for a man with 6 fingers. It is perhaps the finest of it's kind ever to dance in battle.
Crackling with the energy from the angry skies, this club was forged by barbarian shaman for their mightiest of warriors.
Short Blade of the Ardent Tracker
Long Blade of the Ardent Tracker

This blade drips with a virulance that can infect those it strikes with a vicious blood rage. Those infected often strike out at friend and foe alike, or end up staying stationary, consumed with their own anger.

The cruel tip of this whip seems almost alive. It often seeks out the joints and hamstrings of the wielder's foes, slashing tendon and joint, making it hard for the foe to move and inflicting a poison that further limits their maneuverability.
Often wielded by the elite of the smallfolks armies. Many a foe has been surprised by the speed and power that such small troops can possess.

Forged from an amalgam of Mithral and adamantine using a technique unknown outside of Kraag's workshop. Taking several months for the weapon to be completed due to the intricacies of the process. It is a weapon that is under-estimated only once.
Created by using a magical formula almost the opposite of that involved in creating a Golden circlet. The weapon forces waves of psychic disrupters into the opponents mind with each hit.
Noblock was a master thief and guildmaster of the slums. He first comissioned this weapon for his lieutenants, who repaid him by leaving him floating, face down, in the harbour barely a month later.

Forged using secret techniques involving immersion within the four elements and blessings from a grand druid. These weapons are a blessing from, and fill the wielder with a duty to defend, nature and all her bounties.

Created for especially sadistic gladiatorial combats, the trident earned the monicker of Gladiators bane due to the horrific wounds that could be inflicted whilst at the same time healed by the magic of the weapon. Blood loss in battles featuring these weapons was such that only the most bloodthirsty of tournaments would allow this weapon to be used.
Originally created for the warlord, Unthank the mighty, this weapon is designed to intimidate it's foes as quickly as it cuts them down.

Developed by dwarven engineers seeking to help thier armies in battle against the Elven archers of old. Though they never matched the Elven archers, this great metal construct meant that they were able to suppress their enemies long enough for their slow moving troops to reach the front line mostly intact.
A recent innovation in Gnomish tinkering, the techbow is not only a very good bow, it also is capable of emitting a displacement field capable of fending off the attacks of other archers.
Created by the finest Hin craftsmen and women. Though not quite a rival to the finest Elven creations this bow is still formidable indeed.
Calling upon primal forces of magical energy, this staff allows the wielder to unleash fury both near and far.
Enchantments abound in the realms of magic, but some have trouble with the incantations. This staff allows the user to charm or even dominate another, eliminating the need to study the spells.

Forged from Rubicite and Ruby, this ring has a glow about it that can even penetrate the darkness for the wearer, and seems to almost actually absorb blows to the wearer.
